{"DISCHARGE":[{"def":"To relieve of a charge, load, or burden; to empty of a load or cargo; to unburden; to unload; as, to discharge a vessel.","pos":""},{"def":"To free of the missile with which anything is charged or loaded; to let go the charge of; as, to discharge a bow, catapult, etc.","pos":""}],"DISCHARGER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, discharges.","pos":""}],"DISCHURCH":[{"def":"To deprive of status as a church, or of membership in a church.","pos":""}]}